    <!-- About Section -->
    <section id="about" class="py-24 bg-slate-50">
        <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
            <div class="text-center mb-16">
                <h2 class="text-4xl navy-text mb-4 uppercase tracking-tight">About The Conclave</h2>
                <div class="h-1.5 w-24 saffron-bg mx-auto rounded-full"></div>
            </div>

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 mb-16">
                <!-- Conference Aim & Objectives -->
                <div class="space-y-8">
                    <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-gray-100">
                        <h3 class="text-2xl navy-text mb-4 flex items-center gap-2"><i data-lucide="target" class="saffron-text"></i> Aim</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed text-justify">
                            The primary aim of NEEDHIKKALAM 2026 is to ignite a rigorous intellectual movement among the law students, transforming them from passive observers into active contributors to nation building. It strives to equip the next generation of legal leaders with the foresight, patriotism, and technical expertise required steering Bharat towards global leadership by the centenary of its independence.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-navy-bg text-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-lg">
                        <h3 class="text-2xl text-white mb-4 flex items-center gap-2"><i data-lucide="crosshair" class="saffron-text"></i> Objectives</h3>
                        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed list-disc pl-5">
                            <li>Critically analyze the BNS, BNSS, and BSA, exploring how indigenous legal thought can replace colonial legacies.</li>
                            <li>Define legal infrastructures necessary for Bharat's rise as a Vishwa Guru (IPR, AI, Cyber Law).</li>
                            <li>Create a dynamic interface between student delegates and veterans of the Bar, Bench, and legislature.</li>
                            <li>Groom a cadre of young leaders capable of defending Bharat's strategic interests on the global stage.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Organizers -->
                <div class="space-y-8">
                    <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border-l-8 border-orange-500">
                        <h3 class="text-2xl navy-text mb-4">About FOTLAWS</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed text-justify">
                            FOTLAWS is Tamil Nadu's premier student-led forum and think-tank, designed to bridge the gap between legal education and practical nation-building. We unify aspiring jurists, transforming them into active contributors committed to Bharat's developmental aspirations. Driven by a "Nation First" attitude, our mission extends legal practice beyond courtrooms to policy drafting and governance.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border-l-8 border-blue-900">
                        <h3 class="text-2xl navy-text mb-4">About VIT School of Law</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed text-justify">
                            Established in 2014, the VIT School of Law (BCI Approved) aims to impart quality legal education that goes beyond textbooks. It focuses on equipping students with the practical nuances of the profession. Significantly, the School's evaluation system marks a paradigm shift from traditional rote learning, prioritizing the testing of analytical skills and professional competence.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

